#TheWashingtonPost - Trump’s Education Department nixes Obama-era grant program for school diversity.  President Trump’s Education Department has decided to nix an Obama-era grant program meant to help local districts devise ways to boost socioeconomic diversity within their schools, a program that some advocates considered a barometer of the new administration’s commitment to integrated classrooms. An Education Department official said the $12 million grant program was discontinued because it would not be a wise use of tax dollars, in part because the money was to be used for planning, not implementation. Infinite blues 🗺 - - Arraial do Cabo is a municipality located in the #Brazilian state of #RiodeJaneiro. Its population was 27,715 as of 2010 census and its total area is 160 square kilometres (62 sq mi). It was founded in 1503 by the conqueror Amerigo Vespucci. In 1960 a documentary film was made directed by Mário Carneiro and Paulo Cesar Saraceni about the local fishing industry.  Its geography made Arraial do Cabo an important and dangerous point in the age of sail. Since the Portuguese Navy arrival (1503) until nineteenth century many shipwrecks occurred. CINEMATEQUE Nosferatu (1922) Önce edebiyat sonra sinema tarihinin en önemli vampir kahramanı Dracula'nın ilk film versiyonlarından olan Nosferatu, çağına göre oldukça ürkünç ve görsel zenginliğiyle dolu bir sinema başyapıtı. Beyazperdenin ilk vampiri olma saygınlığını kazanan Nosferatu, aynı zamanda ünlü Dracula'nın da öncüleyicisi olarak ortaya çıkar. Bir emlakçı, genç eşini evde bırakarak, Karpat'ların tepelerinde bir şatoda yaşayan gizemli kont Nosferatu'nun yanına gider. Kısa zamanda kontun bir vampir olduğunu anlayan adam, aynı zamanda eşini  de bu canavardan korumak için savaşacaktır... Alman sinemasının tipik Dışavurumcu öğeleri olan; karanlık aydınlık karşıtlığını, bozulmuş perspektif ve yapay dekorları, çarpıtılmış görüntü düzenlemelerini başarıyla kullanan film, aynı zamanda hem yönetmeni Murnau'nun hem de korku türünün ilk önemli başyapıtlarından biri olma özelliğini kazanır. 🎬🎬🎬🎬🎬🎬🎬🎬🎬 Adapted from Bram Stocker's novel "Dracula" Nosferatu is the one of first vampire stories of cinema history with great German Expressionism in cinema of Murnau... Wisbourg, Germany based estate agent Knock dispatches his associate, Hutter, to Count Orlok's castle in Transylvania as the Count wants to purchase an isolated house in Wisbourg. Hutter leaves his innocent wife, Ellen, with some friends while he is away. Hutter's trek is an unusual one, with many locals not wanting to take him near the castle where strange events have been occurring. Once at the castle, Hutter does manage to sell the Count the house, but he also notices and feels unusual occurrences, primarily feeling like there is a dark shadow hanging over him, even in the daytime when the Count is unusually asleep. Hutter eventually sees the Count's sleeping chamber in a crypt, and based on a book he has recently read, believes the Count is really a vampire or Nosferatu. While Hutter is trapped in the castle, the Count, hiding in a shipment of coffins, makes his way to Wisbourg, causing death along his way, which most attribute to the plague. Hutter himself tries to rush home to save his town and most importantly save Ellen from Nosferatu's imminent arrival.  Dir: F.W Murnau Cast: Max schreck, Greta Schröde

#TheWashingtonPost - An undocumented immigrant hanged himself after 3 months in an ICE detention center.  Osmar Epifanio Gonzalez-Gadba was discovered March 22 hanging in his cell at the Adelanto Detention Facility in Adelanto, Calif., about 80 miles northeast of Los Angeles, according to authorities. After officials called 911, the 32-year-old — who has had been in ICE custody since December — was rushed to Victor Valley Global Medical Center’s intensive care unit in Victorville, Calif., and placed on life support, authorities said. Gonzalez-Gadba died early Tuesday morning at the same facility, officials said, six days after his suicide attempt. Authorities said he is the fifth detainee to die in ICE custody in fiscal year 2017. “There are officers and medical personnel who make rounds regularly,” Virginia Kice, an ICE spokeswoman, told The Washington Post. “But in a case like his, this individual was housed in a one-person room, so he was alone when it occurred and they discovered him fairly quickly. “He used a bedsheet tied around his neck to hang himself — that happens very quickly,” Kice added. “We have personnel who monitor all of the residential areas and the facility twenty-four/seven.” #Thursday #Morning #News #ICE #Trump #Refugee #WhiteHouse #democrats #republicans #democracy #instagram #instanews #cnn #foxnews #tyt #nbc #cbs #abc #wgn #love #chicago #lgbt #lgbtq

#TheWashingtonPost - Trump EPA declines to ban pesticide that Obama had proposed outlawing.  The new head of the Environmental Protection Agency refused Wednesday to ban a commonly used pesticide that the Obama administration had sought to outlaw based on mounting concerns about its risks to human health. The chemical compound chlorpyrifos, also known as Lorsban, has been used by farmers for more than a half-century to kill pests on crops including broccoli, strawberries and citrus. The EPA banned its spraying indoors to combat household bugs more than a decade ago. But only in recent years did the agency seek to ban its use in agriculture, after mounting scientific evidence that prenatal exposure can pose risks to fetal brain and nervous system development. A federal judge had given the EPA until Friday to decide whether to finalize its ban of the pesticide.On Wednesday, EPA Administrator Scott Pruitt decided the answer would be no. “We need to provide regulatory certainty to the thousands of American farms that rely on chlorpyrifos, while still protecting human health and the environment,” Pruitt said in a statement. “By reversing the previous administration’s steps to ban one of the most widely used pesticides in the world, we are returning to using sound science in decision-making — rather than predetermined results.” His statement argued that the “public record lays out serious scientific concerns and substantive process gaps in the proposal.” #Thursday #Morning #News #EPA #Environment #Nature #Earth #Planet #instagram #instanews #cnn #foxnews #tyt #nbc #cbs #abc #wgn #love #chicago #lgbt #lgbtq

Last year Jon decided to play the ultimate prank on me for April Fool's. I need suggestions to get him back. ------------------ I'm deathly afraid of birds. Deathly. I run across the street to avoid them, I cry at the zoo when I see them. Well Jon decided to have a random number text me my parrot delivery was going to be at my place at 7. I freaked out. He had this number call me to confirm the delivery. I paced for about an hour in my apartment crying. I called my best friend, my parents and Jon screaming. Finally, my door man calls me, and says I need to come get my delivery. Turns out that little brat had Chik Fil A delivered to me. A dead bird cooked and with a side of a shake, I can work with that. Now it's on to get him back.

#Repost @carlajian ・・・ Isn't this the cutest mug shot?  Raising a toddler is hard work and it feels like everything takes a little longer when you're with a mini human that's always asking "what dis?". On the bright side it does remind me to slow down.  This past weekend I shared an Instagram story of Mason jumping in puddles for the first time...which prompted a trip to @zara for clean pants.  Yesterday he was fascinated with the seating area or what he thought was an indoor park at the @realgoodjuiceco @southportcorridorchicago.  He also likes to stop to look at flowers, and then with his cute little hands sign "flower". I'm busy, you're busy, we are ALL busy.  How about we slow down a bit, and create a little space to be completely present?  Lately I've been rushing my meals. Not looking at my food, or even standing and trying to multitask in between bites.  I love food, and I didn't event take the time to enjoy it 🤦🏻‍♀️. What are you rushing through?  What thing(s) in your day can you adjust to make it less crazy?  Please share below 👇 I bet it's something we all need to be more aware of so we feel less 😖and more 😌.

Yesterday was my last long call day of my first year of residency. It's been an incredibly difficult year that cannot possibly be measured in the number of hours I've worked, the number of patients I've seen, or in the number of notes I've written. Over the past several months I have gained even more of an appreciation for medicine and the art that it is. No matter how much science dictates what we do from day to day, patients will ultimately remember who you are, how you speak to them, and most importantly how you listen. A tip to any future doctor, nurse, or any other health care professional reading this... Always be kind. Always treat others with the respect that you would want. Always keep in mind that your patient is someone's mom/sister/brother/friend/lover... it'll go a long way and it will make your job infinitely more rewarding. #medicine #doctor #sandiego #cali #california #la #losangeles #flowers #lajolla #delmar #photo #photography #photooftheday #travel #traveling #travelphotography #ny #nyc #miami #philly #philadelphia #chicago #chitown #sanfrancisco #sfs

Spotlight on Teaching Artist Maya Trujillo! @_mayaluna_77 began her aerial training in San Miguel de Allende, Mexico at the age of 17 with the circus troupe Gravity Works. At 21 she moved to the United States and took Teacher Training Courses at NECCA in Vermont with Serenity Forchion and Elsie Smith. She began teaching at ADC in January of 2016 and has taught all ages on several different apparatuses. She believes that everyone learns differently, but without a doubt, everyone is able to learn. 'Tomorrow'  This is my third attempt  at a poem today.  The thoughts are there  mocking and teasing, fornicating in earnest  bearing bastard children  that hide  in made-up cardboard boxes,  in made-up back alleys, inside my mind.  They're usually quite anxious  to come out and play.  Not today.  Perhaps its their asshole father,  stress,  that drives them invisible.  I hear their whispers,  quiet chuckles and gasps,  from inside each box.  I'll let them play,  and enjoy the day in their own way.  Maybe I'll see them tomorrow,  and write  a better poem.  #poetry #poetsofinstagram #writersofinstagram #wordporn #wordgasm #spilledink #spilledinkpoetry #original #poem #poet #android #androidonly #driving #Chicago #fog #foggyday

Because I want you to follow & support @LTMFOUNDATION, a local addiction awareness and overdose prevention foundation named after Louie Miceli, a young man who died at age 24 due to heroin overdose. An overdose can happen to anyone including YOU, even on your first time trying certain drugs like cocaine & heroin. Talk to your kids about drugs. Why is it so important to have these kinds of sometimes awkward conversations? Because you never know whose life you may impact.  Addiction impacts everyone who comes in contact with an addict, especially family & friends. It can be an overwhelming, stressful and difficult time that affects relationships, health & even faith. In keeping with our core mission to provide support for those affected by addiction, LTM hosts a monthly support group for families to provide a lifeline for those seeking information, understanding & compassion in a confidential, non-judgmental environment.  Support Groups provide a supportive environment to: > Enhance coping skills > Promote self-care > Provide psychoeducation > Offer guidance and resources. Join us every fourth Thursday of each month from 7-8pm at 1244 West Army Trail Road, Carol Stream, IL.  #LTMFoundation #LTMSupportGroups  #LTMVolunteer  #TheRealRoxanne  #HopeDealer  #FuckHeroin

Today is a birthday of a genius and a dreamer.  His art is clear and free. Most of the people thought that he was a nonentity, an eccentric, or an unpleasant person — somebody who had no position in society until his death. Even though then society did not recognize him, in his work you can see love based more on a feeling of serenity, than on passion. In his artwork, you can feel misery that is reborn into calmness, pure harmony, and music.  I see beautiful moments in the poorest cottages, in the dirtiest corners. Where there are real feelings and real life. And my mind is driven towards these things with an irresistible momentum. I guess he would love to visit Ukraine. Honestly, I can't​ count five Black men that I personally know that have never been arrested at some point in their life.  I was arrested as teenager in Chicago at 17yrs old, the police found nothing, but decided to arrest me anyway, and at the station they told me they would put in the report that I was in possession of cannibis so they could process me . (What transpired during the arrest was much more chaotic than this sanitized synopsis, let's just say I could have easily been #philandocastile #altonsterling or another #victim of #chicago #police department.) I spent the night was cold, tried but didn't sleep, had a bologna sandwich, and got out the next day. Fortunately the Judge dismissed the case a month later or so... Fortunately for me the "dismissed misdamenor for cannibis possession" did not drastically impact my life or employment.. However, I wonder how different my life might be today if instead of the police charging me for cannibis.. suppose I was planted with crack or cocaine or heroin, or they said I committed some other haneous crime burglary, rape. Suppose it was felony and I was found guilty or forced into a plea deal (where you accept a guilty plea and get a dramatically shorter prison sentence)..I would not have been interviewed let alone hired to work for General Electric, Motorola, Anheuser Busch..Fortunately for me those j.o.b.s (just over broke) positioned me to be able to pursue entreprenual endeavors with some basic financial reserves.. Once a person is convicted of a felony in the #unitedstates you can legally discriminate against them in Housing, employment, professionally, politically and so on for their entire life.. Additionally there are a host of negative effects it has on their families and children.  The #truth is many of our #brothers and #sisters and trapped by in the system are #innocent... Just sending some love to all those behind bars  for doing absolutely nothing. #love

"Medicinal plants meant the difference between life and death for many soldiers and civilians during the Civil War. Take a walk back in time at Frying Pan Farm Park on April 1 and search for the plants that helped a generation survive.  According to the Civil War Trust, death from wounds and disease was an additional burden of the war that took a toll on the hearts, minds, and bodies of all Americans, but it also sped up the progression of medicine and influenced practices the Army and medical practitioners still use today.  While the Union certainly had the advantage of better medical supplies and manpower, both Rebels and Federals attempted to combat illness and improve medical care for their soldiers during the war. Many of America’s modern medical accomplishments have their roots in the legacy of America’s defining war.  According to Patricia B. Mitchell, author of the book “Civil War Plants and Herbs,” as the Civil War conflict intensified, the citizenry of both sides scrambled for resources.  Creative plant-derived alternatives for traditional food, clothing, household products, and pharmaceutical supplies were sought and developed. The South, especially, turned to the land for help as the Union blockade tightened and fields and orchards were being laid to waste..." #garden #medicinalplants #plantlife #plantbased #plants #gardening #wellbeing #wellness #thankyoucreator #medicine #heal #healing #safety #life #wayoflife #motherearth #naturespharmacy #remedy #blood #injury #vancouver #toronto #war #humanrights #alternative #natural #newyork #chicago #seattle #growyourownmedicine

"If you’re displeased with the actions of your representatives in Congress, you typically have to wait until the next election to try to hold them accountable. But in light of the recent approval of Senate Joint Resolution 34, voters are fighting back in a more creative way.  The Resolution, which passed narrowly with only Republican votes in both the Senate and the House, repeals regulations put in place under former President Barack Obama in 2016 that said internet service providers had to ask for consumers’ permission before selling their personal information to third parties.  Customers’ “sensitive private information” includes browsing histories, precise geo-locations and even financial and medical data, according to the Federal Communications Commission. The Resolution becomes law once it’s signed by President Donald Trump.  The votes caused outrage among internet communities such as Reddit, and now some activists have announced plans to fight Republicans – by using the law Congress just passed.  Adam McElhaney, a self-described privacy activist and net neutrality advocate from Chattanooga, Tennessee, established a Go Fund Me page to raise money to buy the internet histories of members of Congress. Once he has them, he says he plans to publish them online so anyone can search through them. He raised more than $160,000 within four days. “Help me raise money to buy the histories of those who took away your right to privacy for just thousands of dollars from telephone and ISPs. Your private data will be bought and sold to marketing companies, law enforcement,” McElhaney wrote in the Go Fund Me. “Let’s turn the tables. Let’s buy THEIR history and make it available.”..." #government #patriotact #privacy #usa #newyork #portland #seattle #chicago #internet #miami #dallas #boise #maine #florida #losangeles #sandiego #sanfrancisco #reclaimyourpower #standup #corruption #trump #canada #vancouver #boulder #detroit #michigan #ohio #columbus #humanrights #doublestandards

Knowing the proper times to comb your beard is important. You want to avoid combing your beard while it's  wet to avoid hair loss. If you already have a thinner beard, combing it while it's wet could make it worse. You also want to avoid vigorous combing while blow drying your beard as well. When the hair is hot, it allows the hair follicle to be ripped out straight from the root with ease. Obviously, you want to avoid that as well. The key here is to towel dry your beard (if you must), but do so in a patting motion to avoid creating split ends. Once the excess water is removed, use a proper comb for your beard type to gently stroke it through your beard. If blow drying your beard, simply allow a little time to let your beard cool off before continuing your routine to avoid unwanted hair removal.  #tdcbeardco #tdcbeardfacts #beardedmen #beardlove #beardedgentleman #beardeddragon #beard #bearded #sale #beardoil #beardbalm #classic #facialpaintbrush #beardgang #altantabarbers #atl #chicago #houstonbarber #houston #newengland #ny #losangeles #la #insta #photographer #beardlife #detroit #beardnation #hair #dapper

Mies van der Rohe - 5. Having arrived in the US, Mies van der Rohe settled in Chicago to run the architecture school at the new Illinois Institute of Technology, and to design the master plan for its campus and its new buildings. Mies’s first projects in the US were all for IIT, starting with the Minerals and Metals Building, completed in early 1943. He described the design and construction process as requiring a “Herculean effort to adapt to the new conditions of building in America” and struggled to cope with the wartime restrictions on materials. By the late 1940s, Mies had adapted to the US system and wartime constraints were easing. When he was invited to design a weekend retreat on the Fox River for Edith Farnsworth, a dashingly sophisticated doctor, he had met at a cocktail party, Mies produced one of the most exquisite and ingenious buildings of his career. The Farnsworth House consists of two parallel horizontal planes and gigantic glass walls supported by eight steel columns to create a minimal structure raised above the ground that opens up the interior with the natural beauty of its surroundings, and vice versa. It took 167 drawings for Mies to develop the design. Edith Farnsworth proved to be a charismatic and intellectually stimulating client. She and Mies became firm friends, and were rumoured to be lovers. But as Mies obsessed over the details of the house, the project went way over schedule and exceeded its $40,000 budget. By the time the house was completed in 1951, he and Edith had fallen out. #design #architecture #miesvanderrohe #chicago #illinoisinstituteoftechnology #dredithfarnsworth @illinoistech @farnsworthhouse #opulentmodernism

Amazon CEO Jeff Bezos laid out his plans for space tourism and the future of Blue Origin, his reusable rocket company, at the 33rd annual Space Symposium in Colorado Springs on Wednesday. The world's second richest person plans to make its New Shepard vehicle ready for consumer spaceflight by 2018. Bezos believes reusable rockets are the key to getting "millions of people living and working in space." He explained that these rockets can endure more practice runs, which leads to more learning, and, hopefully, faster innovation. Bezos also plans to sell about $1 billion a year of Amazon stock to fund Blue Origin. The Lowell 6:40 is the busiest train.  The MBTA fiscal management control board voted last summer to give Keolis at least $66 million more over its eight-year contract.  BostonMagazine.com -Commuter Rail Operator Blames Delays, Cancellations on Defects in New Trains  We’ve got ourselves a bunch of lemons.  #Embargo presents #Keolis #MBTA #MaPoli #WashingtonDCTheBestRealityShowonTV  For the second morning in a row, the MBTA had to cancel four commuter rail trains Thursday. The problem? We’ve been sold a bunch of lemons.  Commuter rail operator Keolis says the rash of poor service can be attributed to recently discovered defects in eight of their 40 new locomotives. After just two years in service, these little-engines-that-can’t are plagued with mechanical issues, leaving Keolis without the appropriate number of trains for full service, the Globe reports.  The Stoughton 6:20 a.m. inbound train, Lowell 6:40 a.m. inbound train, Newburyport/Rockport 8:33 a.m. inbound train, and Rockport 6:39 a.m. outbound train were canceled Thursday morning, while the Franklin 7:40 a.m. and 7:50 a.m. inbound trains were delayed. “A combination of equipment shortages due to mechanical issues and other equipment unable to move due to a trespasser strike in the evening have necessitated the cancellation of these trains,” Keolis said in a statement. “We have worked throughout the night to mitigate issues surrounding morning service delivery and continue to work to address the issue.” According to the Boston Globe, only 27 of the 40 locomotives the MBTA bought two years ago, are currently running.  At least eight of them have a defective engine component that is currently being replaced.  #NewYorkCity #WashingtonDC #Hartford #Indianapolis #Cleveland #Chicago #Seattle #Denver #Detroit #Louisville #Cincinnati #Philadelphia #Pittsburgh #Minneapolis #Miami #Atlanta #Dallas #Nashville #Boston #Baltimore #Richmond #KansasCity

Сегодня я похожа на этих малышей)) развенчиваем стереотипы о прекрасах американских городов: погода в Бостоне в начале апреля по-питерски очаровательна)))) весь день по прогнозу дождь, ветер и всего 4 градуса... Да и вообще мне не понятно, почему американцы, как только услышат, что ты из России, сразу говорят, что у нас холодно очень. В Нью-Йорке погода зимой просто ужасна (по рассказам наших друзей и не только), в феврале у них холодно, температура опускается до -15, но из-за океана здесь дуют ледяные ветра и выпадает много снега. В Чикаго тоже не очень то))) весной температура скачет неописуемо: НЙ, Чикаго, Бостон - понедельник +10, далее -4, на след день +20, и через день -6. Это реальный прогноз)))) серости и дождей здесь тоже хватает)))))) а про НЙ летом рассказывают: лучше держитесь от него подальше в самую жару, тк на Манхеттане мусор выносят и складывают прямо на улицах города (огромные мешки мусора), улицы и дома нагреваются и все это начинает гнить и благоухать на весь город. В метро в это время еще то удовольствие: вентиляция очень плохая, метро неглубокое и в жаркий летный день ты выходишь из метро как из сауны))))) #newyork #chicago #boston #weather #rainyday

The power of portions... the spoon on the right is DOUBLE!  Thanks to @erinoprea (@carrieunderwood's trainer aka she's amazing) for posting something like this last week- it really hit home for me! ESP because it was peanut butter! Guilty pleasure. Sometimes we mindlessly eat, or eat a ton of food just because it's "clean." If you're wondering why you can't lose weight, bottom line is even what looks like a little bit  more can be damaging to your goals.  Trust me, I struggle with this just as much as anyone! I used to think it was either:  1. Count macros and eat whatever junk you want (donuts, sugar free syrups in coffee, etc.) OR  2. Eat clean and eat as much as you want, which is why Whole 30 wasn't great for me personally... hello huge portions of real food!  I've been realizing lately that the sweet spot is counting macros and eating clean! Portion sizes AND healthy food is the best way to go for me right now, based on my goals. Find what works for you!

~Coach Cappelli’s Keys to the Game~ 1. Duck and Cover - The Blackhawks will take on the Anaheim Ducks for their second to last game of the regular season. Each team has won one of the two meetings this season, so tonight will be the tie breaker. Each meetup has also been decided by only one goal, with the Hawks first beating the Ducks 3-2 and the Ducks more recently shutting the Hawks out 1-0. Once again, this game doesn’t matter for the Hawks, as they are already locked into place for playoffs, so they’ll want to make sure they stay safe and that no one gets hurt.  2. Who Getz the last Laf - Ryan Getzlaf has been picking up the points lately, so don’t expect him to stay quiet against the Blackhawks tonight. He has six assists and a goal in his last five games. Four of those assists game in a single game against the Rangers on March 26th. He leads the team in points and assists, so he’ll need to be shut down early and as often as possible tonight.  3. Hart on my sleeve - Ryan Hartman will look to become the seventh Blackhawk to reach at least 20 goals in this season. He scored his 19th of this year against the Avalanche on Tuesday night and also recorded an assist against the Penguins on March 29th. He’s looking to get ready for playoffs, so look to him to step up big time tonight.  4. Born and Bread - Artemi Panarin once again notched the Hawks’ opening goal on Tuesday night, though the Hawks did eventually fall to the Avs. It was the fifth straight game where the winger had tallied the Hawks’ first goal of the game. With the roster missing lots of the Hawks’ traditional stars tonight (Toews, Hossa, etc..), also expect Panarin to have some fun showing off. He’s the first in Blackhawks history to kick off his career with consecutive 30-goal seasons, so now he just gets to run with it and have a little fun before the true test of playoffs begin. #hawks #hockey #hawkey #hawkeytown #letsgohawks #gohawksgo #blackhawks #chicago #chicagoblackhawks #nhl #hawksvsducks #keystothegame

Justin heard about Soul City Church from long time friends and recently began calling Soul City Church his home. His story tells us how a simple invitation led him to experience the love of God and transformed the trajectory of his life. . . . . . . . I know what it’s like to be abandoned by a father. My dad left when I was two, and I was raised by my mom. We regularly attended a Catholic church until one day, a friend invited my mom to join a small group at another church, which we started attending weekly. I was a bit of a weird kid and didn't do well in new environments. On my first Sunday, I was invited to a youth group retreat and decided to go. At the retreat, I saw kids my age worshiping Jesus, and that flooded me with questions. My youth leader took me under his wing and took time to genuinely listen to me -- not just tell me what to believe. I eventually shared with him about my dad and was brought to tears of anger and heavy resentment that I hadn't dealt with. He quietly shared that there was someone who would never abandoned me. For the first time, Jesus was real to me. During Jesus' final moments on the cross, He says "My God, my God why have you forsaken me?" That gets me every time. I know what it feels like to be separated from my father, and it's awesome to think that Jesus willingly endured the cross so that I would never have to be separated from my heavenly Father.  After college, I fell away from God. In some ways I'm still dealing with the consequences of those times, but as I look back, the sequence of events just doesn't make sense. All along, God has blessed me with people to lead me back to Him. A few weeks ago, I was baptized again. That marked an end of eight years of being away from God. I've lived life without God before, and I can't make that mistake again. I'm so thankful to know that I am not alone in this journey, and that God continues to redeem and restore what I've thought I'd lost so many years ago. . . . . . "God so loved the world, so I could love my world." Who are you inviting to Easter this year? A simple invitation can change someone's life!

While I post plenty of skateboarding videos of myself and friends, I've been looking to make it more of a goal of mine to post more photos of my "amateur" work, skate/snow related or not, for all to see.  It's the perfectionist's dilemma. Waiting for the perfect shot, moment, or time to share your work. And in anticipating that moment, it never comes to pass, where no eyes ever see it other than your own.  Then what's the point?  If there's one recurring life theme I've learned so far, the "timing" you're waiting for, will never be right. Just go and do, and adjust course along the way. Whatever that might be.  That trip you always wanted to take? Book it. The person you haven't spoken to in a while? Give em' a ring. It's an undervalued lesson that mistakes, in our efforts to avoid them, paradoxically are the best way to move us forward.  That being said, I hope whatever it is you guys are pursuing is the thing you wouldn't mind picking yourself back up from again and again. Do what you love, and despite how many missteps and slip ups you encounter, do it unapologetically and do it with a smile.  @dashawnjordan - Bump to Noseslide at Damn Am Chicago last summer.  #tbt #chicago #skateboarding

The perspective they give. The knowledge, wisdom and truth. I appreciate bloggers a lot. Today as I spent time doing my quiet time, I stumbled across the question, "how are you glorify God?" I don't know why but I had to stop and think about it. God wants all of me. Which means in all that I do, He should be glorified. God just doesn't want parts of us, He wants ALL of us. In our daily surrenders of choosing to follow Him. The gift of grace and redemption of this new life that He has given us, shouldn't be used so effortless. But for us to be examples to those around us. Living a life glorifying to God, is not supposed to be easy. We are tempted, we get lost, we do dumb things and we are broken. But we have a God who overlooks our past mistakes. A God who is able to renew and transform our hearts. It's not going to be an easy journey and it wasn't meant to be. Walk along side those who will be able to encourage and speak truth into your life. And be grateful for the handful of people that have been walking along side you.

United Springs of America #🌸 #🇺🇸 Давеча приняла участие в опросе.  Хотела вежливо отказаться, и такую вот шикарную на мой взгляд отмазу, транслирую,  мол, инглиш мой не настолько гут, опасаюсь,  вдруг что не пойму и отвечу не так.  Да, конечно, а какой ваш родной язык? Русский, говорю. А, ноу проблем, держите опросник на русском.  Всего 10 минут.  И 50 баксов можно выиграть в лотерею среди респондентов.  Такая забота в частности обо мне, возможность ощутить себя респондентом, вместе с гипотетическим полтинником - и вот я сижу отвечаю на вопросы.  Ну что. Обещанные 10 минут я размышляла над вторым вопросом. А именно.  Ваш пол: Мужчина Женщина  Трансгендер  Другое  Что это за #другое такое, а??? Иное? Нейтральное? Никакое? А называть - оно?  Тут, в инстаграме,  вон целый движняк на тему недоженственных женщин,  и недомужественных мужчин.  Так может это все разновидности этого вот,  другого? Типа #недоженщина или #напутикженщине или  #неопределилась ОЙ #неопределилось  По первичным половым признакам, как я себе представляю,  ничего другого существовать не должно. Хотя мои представлении похоже довольно узкие,  так что #хз  А если по ощущениям отвечать на такой вопрос, то тут лучше не давать волю #фантазии  Или может,  так произошло: - Your sex? - Одним словом описать? Секундочку... 😂  В общем, по итогам размышлений, я решительной закорючкой отнесла себя к женщинам.  #нуаче  И не думала, что половая идентификация такая неоднозначная и сложная тема😂  #этоамерикадетка #чикагогородконтрастов #дневникистранствующегосемейства

The Crown Fountain in Chicago, designed by Spanish artist Jaume Plensa, is a great example of the wonderful Chicago's public art collection. It consists of two 50 foot glass block towers at each end of a black granite reflecting pool. The towers use LEDs to display video images from a broad social spectrum of Chicago citizens, and having water flow through an outlet in the screen to give an illusion of water spouting from their mouths. Such a great feature in Chicago's Millennium Park. #thecrownfountain #millenniumpark #chicago #illinois #chicagopublicart #jaumeplensa

A rare original drawing of Tintin from the comic book album “Tintin in America” sold for 753,000 euros ($798,000) on Saturday in Paris, the Artcurial auction house said.  The 21x15 cm (8.2 x 5.9 inch) China ink drawing by the Belgian cartoonist known as Herge, one of four colour plates of the 1937 edition of the book, was valued at between 600,000 and 700,000 euros.  The drawing, sold with its colour overlay, shows the intrepid boy reporter, revolver in hand, standing on the running board of a speeding taxi chasing evil-doers in the streets of Chicago.#tintin #cartoon #drawing #auction #herge #drawings #sketch #art #instaart #artists #instagram #instacartoon #cartoonist #belgian #chicago

What a day! I am so blessed to be able to cross souls like @dylanwerneryoga in my life. He has an intelligent, safe, and experienced teaching style, prioritizing what is important: the contents, not the container. BIG respect goes out to him and all teachers who openly admit they were wrong in the past, and pass no judgment on themselves for it. Мне задали вопрос: "Как ты успеваешь узнавать о всех новинках в мире бизнеса и не только?". Отвечаю.  1. Когда есть свободная минута (стою в очереди, еду в метро, кого-то ожидаю), я читаю статьи на телефоне. Считаю это самой свежей информацией по сравнению с книгами и прочими материалами.  2. Когда заняты руки (иду пешком по улице, еду на велосипеде и т.д.), слушаю в наушниках интервью с предпринимателями и другими интересными людьми.  3. Когда завтракаю, обедаю или ужинаю без компании, смотрю видео с выступлениями на конференциях. Считаю это самым эффективным способ получения информации с конференций. Личное посещение конференций только с целью новых знакомств.  4. Когда есть время и руки свободны (еду в такси, ожидаю встречи и т.д.), читаю книги. Аудио книги не люблю, т.к. хорошая книга генерирует новые идеи и мысли, которые я люблю записывать и обращаться к ним повторно по мере необходимости.  Ежедневно интересные статьи мне падают в Pocket, поэтому я всегда знаю что читать без затрат времени на поиск. Видео с конференций мне падают на YouTube в список "Посмотреть позже", поэтому всегда есть что смотреть. Подкасты я слушаю в мобильном приложении "Podcast & Radio Addict", выбрав интересую категорию. А книги читаю на электронной читалке от Amazon, в которой загружено сотни книг, и этот список регулярно пополняю.  Читайте больше и с удовольствием ;) #chicago #illinois #usa

Сегодня у меня гостевой пост с очень интересной личностью @imjustcuriousblog .  Ира Желяско уехала из Одессы жить и учиться в ТОРОНТО чуть меньше года назад. • ❤️ LIKE & FOLLOW если хотите продолжения! ❤️ ___ Мы решили поделиться с вами постом "Топ-3 вещей, которые Ире НРАВЯТСЯ В КАНАДЕ". У неё на странице @imjustcuriousblog можете прочитать мой гостевой пост "Топ-3 вещей, которые мне НЕ НРАВЯТСЯ В США" А на следующей неделе мы поменяемся местами. Итак, поехали: • 🇨🇦 3 вещи, которые мне НРАВЯТСЯ в Канаде • 1️⃣ ВЕЖЛИВОСТЬ И ДОБРОЖЕЛАТЕЛЬНОСТЬ ЛЮДЕЙ| Знаете, какое любимое слово у любого канадца (помимо восклицания eh 😄)? Sorry. Они его говорят всем, всегда и везде. Иногда мне кажется, что даже если ты целенаправленно собьёшь канадца с ног, он скажет Сорри, ей-богу 😅 Ну, а про всем известную улыбку и Hello, how are you? я рассказывать не буду - все и так в курсе. Не знаю, как в Америке, но в Канаде в большинстве случаев улыбка эта искренняя. ••• 2️⃣ КОМФОРТ| Что уж тут скрывать: Канада - развитая, "удобная" для проживания страна, материально обеспеченная, более-менее стабильная и безопасная. Не зря же она каждый год входит в топы самых лучших стран для проживания в мире 👐🏽 P.S. Местные все равно продолжают потихоньку, но жаловаться. Мне кажется, это естественно, когда ты родился в стране. Особенно не любят они общественный транспорт. Эх, не ездили они в украинских маршрутках 😂 Шеф, заднюю! ••• 3️⃣ ТОЛЕРАНТНОСТЬ| Толерантность проявляется во всем. Начнём с того, что в том же Торонто живут представители половины других национальностей мира 😅 И все мирно сосуществуют, и все уважают друг друга. Религия, цвет кожи, язык, внешний вид - это не имеет значение. Звучит пафосно, но большинство людей действительно не оценивает по внешним факторам! #оБоже Хотите угадать, кто оценивает? Правильно, русские и украинцы 🌚 Ну и то не все - хочешь жить в Канаде, учись быть толерантным к зелёным волосам, татуированным телам и носкам под вьетнамки. Меня саму иногда бесит, что многие из них ходят неаккуратно. Признаюсь честно, про себя могу подумать - мама дорогая, я бы так никогда не оделась. Ну и что? Вот я и не оденусь, это я, а это она. И это её жизнь. ⬇️Продолжение в комментариях ⬇️

It's the best day of the week guyyyys and I am just feeling so so good 🔆 anyone else in an extra good mood today? The lord has been doing some work on my heart recently, so I appreciate you all being patient with me while I took a much needed little break from the blogging world. I have come to learn that moving to a new city isn't easy; in fact it's really really hard... But you know what's even more difficult? Appreciating the good without ever experiencing the not so good. I just got back from visiting home (Colorado) this past weekend and the couple of days I was there were exactly what I needed. Those mountains are just too toooo special ෴ Thankful for such sweet friendships that never change and for a family that is so warm and welcoming no matter how much time has passed -- finally being able to visit home has allowed me to hit the restart button with a more clear and optimistic attitude. I haven't been, but I decided that I need to put my FULL heart into Chicago from here on forward, get out there and explore, meet new people, try out even more new classes, all with an open heart and an open mind -- I feel like this will allow it to truly feel more like home. Anyone else feel like they needed to hit the restart button recently? What kind of things help you restart? *Model call* DM me. Currently in Fort Wayne. Part 1 So, I made post about this in my story about a week or so ago, but I just haven't had time to type it all out in a post, so here goes since I will probably try to find more people to work with this summer.  One of the questions I get the most, is how do I find/approach my models, the beauty part is I don't.... 😂😂😂 I only work with people that come to me, whether it's paid or for a collab. Because 1. I'm a guy and reaching out to people just seems super awkward and could come off creepy, and 2. I don't really want to work with somebody that doesn't know or appreciate my work.  So I let people approach me and then from there, I try to determine how serious they are about shooting/modeling.  I always let people propose their own ideas before I suggest anything. Because I don't know them, their style, taste, comfort zone, or wardrobe. If they say they're up for anything and don't send any examples or ideas I probably won't shoot with them because idk what to expect or suggest. Today was absolutely remarkable. The actors. The music. The feel of the theatre. I may or may not have sobbed the entire time from excitement and INCREDIBLE TALENT. My face hurts from smiling so much my hands ache from how hard I clapped. And I am so sad it's over and now just a memory. It was such a fascinating experience that I am grateful to have been a part of. @mrbradybaby was the perfect Aaron Burr. Talk about an unbelievable last performance. I mean, way to go out with a BANG. 🤣 #literally And @josephamorales as Alexander Hamilton was so awe-inspiring. He was a softer version and brought such a different view to the character. I absolutely loved him and was so grateful to see him in this role.  Truly the entire cast today was TOP NOTCH PERFECTION.  This Chicago trip has been one for the books and I cannot wait to do it all again. #hamilton #hamfam #hamiltonCHI

http://www.surgeryencyclopedia.com/Ce-Fi/Cervical-Cerclage.html I know so many people who are getting pregnant nowadays. If you go into premature labor make sure to ask about this procedure. I don't mean to scare anyone but this comes from my own experience and is heart-felt. Sometimes premature labor happens even if you and your pregnancy are healthy. I wasn't informed about this procedure in my second pregnancy which resulted in me losing my son. In my third pregnancy I was referred to a specialist. I went into premature labor once again but this time my physician talked to me about having a Cerclage put in which is simply stitching your cervix shut so that you wouldn't dilate. We went through with it because you would do anything to give your baby a better chance of survival. My Angel Baby is a success story because of this procedure. If you plan on getting pregnant or already are pregnant, do your research. Things happen sometimes that you aren't prepared for. Get educated so that you and your baby have a better outcome. #marchofdimes #newparents #tampabay #florida #cervicalcerclage #chicago #indiana

Do you recall the lyric in the kung fu 🐼 song " it's a little bit frightening, it's the book of your life that you are writing."?What I find frightening about this lyric is not that we are each responsible for our life story ( that is a given), but that our book may never get finished the way we had originally planned it to once we began writing it. Not all books can have nice neat endings. Therefore, I started thinking about the importance of short stories, or having one big book divided into a few books, or maybe writing a few books at the same time. Or how about a book with an open ending ? Why put such pressure on yourself to have the Hollywood ending? Create your own version of reality, your own recipe to success, and bring more Joy into every part of your life. You can modify today’s pose, Kurmasana, a number of ways: 1) not sliding the arms under and just working on the forward fold at the waist, 2) bending the knees slightly as you fold forward so the spine is straighter and the chest comes closer to the ground, 3) ‘flipping’ the pose and practice something similar laying on your back, then pushing on the heels to bring the toes towards the floor, etc. In all of those we’re trying to increase the bend at the hip flexors while maintaining a (fairly) straight back. This baby #armbalance I propose has the same idea in mind. The biggest issue people have is the final lift off the ground. Climb the legs really high up on the back of the arms (the higher, the easier to go up), drop the forearms on the mat, elbows really close to the body, spread the fingers and, instead of jumping ‘up’ like a spring, project out through the legs and let them ‘take you’ with them… Even if they’re not completely straight, the legs have endless power to take you places, and they will if you let them! Pull the low belly in, flatten your back once more and look out! Give it a try if you want to or try any modification you’d prefer to practice today!! For more modifications and ideas, follow Emma @emma.rhiannon and Paloma @palomahuner. For translation in several languages, follow these accounts daily! The freshman students entering college at the start of the 2017 school year are quite a special generation. Ariyana Davis, a Chicago High School Senior, has been accepted into all 24 colleges she's applied to - 23 of those schools were HBCU's.  Using #CommonBlackCollegeApplication which allows students to apply to up to 50 HBCU's for the one time fee of $35 she was pleasantly surprised at the acceptance to each #HBCU. The one #PWI she applied to and was also accepted into was Eastern Illinois University.  Davis told ABC News it was important to attend an HBCU "because they are known for producing successful black professionals." In total, Davis has received $300,000 in financial aid from the schools she applied to, an opportunity which she is "really grateful" for.  The high schools learning resource coordinator, Julianne Alvarado, remembered Davis since she was a freshman at Mother McAuley Liberal Arts High School. She shared, "I’ve seen her grow, and change, and mature and now that she has this goal for after high school...she went for it," she gushed. "She's very well organized and follows through with things." Ariyana has selected to attended Alcorn State University in Lorman, Mississippi and is majoring in accounting. She said of the university, "I love the family-oriented environment and close-knitted community, and the opportunity they will provide to me when I join the honors courses," Davis said of her decision.  Congrats on your success and good luck in all your future endeavors, Ariyana!! #ReneeAroundTheWay

The benchmark averages have surrendered earlier gains on news that China has deployed 150,000 troops to the North Korean border, and the U.S. is considering further sanctions against Russia. The reports caused the S&P 500 to falter at trendline resistance at 2,370 and the Dow Jones Industrial Average to fall back to support at the 50-day moving average. Stocks were cautiously higher before Monday's open amid geopolitical pressures and jitters ahead of Q1 earnings from the country's largest banks. It was literally raining sideways at this point in Terry and Amanda's wedding day. We had just finished taking pictures inside the church with their families, and we walked outside to cold and rain and wind. So we stood on the steps of the church Amanda grew up in, and using the small bit of shelter the pillars and overhang provided as shelter, Terry kept Amanda warm. While I'm sure he'd done this a million times before that moment, I had the chance to witness the first time he'd done so with her as his wife. The fact that I get to capture these firsts, no matter how seemingly minute, will always feel important to me. #brookealaina #weddingphotography @achuels @t.joria

Ох уже этот Чикаго. Чем больше читаю, тем больше хочется написать. Гуляя по городу, мы не всегда знаем историю того или иного предмета, здания, памятника, скульптуры и тд, который привлекает наше внимание. Как думаете, приятней рассматривать достопримечательность зная ее историю и посыл? Или же, дать волю фантазии, а потом сравнить с фактами и посмотреть что из этого получилось? Я, например, люблю и то и другое. Правда часто мы пропускаем классные места, просто даже не подозревая что именно здесь создавалась история. Оставлю вам эту замечательную фотографию. Пусть каждый прочитает ее по своему!  Oh, Chicago. The more I read, the more I want to write. Walking around the city, sometimes we do not  know the history of a particular object, building, monument, sculpture, etc., which attracts our attention. Do you think it is more pleasant to consider the landmark knowing its history and message? Or, give vent to fantasy, and then compare with facts? For example, I love both. I'll leave you this wonderful photo. Let everyone read it in their own way!  #freelookinfo #chicago #ilike #naturelovers #photography #passionpassport #letsgo #exited #sculpture #arts #history #letsgo #traveling #travelblogger #iloveart #usa #men

The hallmark of any great basketball card collection is the Michael Jordan Fleer rookie. For about seven years, no recognized manufacturer marketed basketball cards. That was until Fleer entered the fray in 1986. The big card was that of Jordan. In the photo Jordan is soaring through the air en route to a slam dunk. Making this particular issue even more desirable, this card features a choice blue felt tip marker signature from MJ across the lower half of the card. With an autograph grade of PSA MINT 9, the offered card also features an authentication from Upper Deck Authenticated (UDA). It is important to note that Jordan NO LONGER SIGNS ROOKIE CARDS! This policy has been in effect for several years, and has been witnessed at several UDA signing events. With MJ's legendary status solidified with a Hall of Fame induction in 2009, rare specimens of his coveted rookie issue are destined for continued growth and present an excellent long term investment opportunity. #MichaelJordan #Jordan #airjordan #hisairness #MJ #chicago #bulls #chicagobulls #basketball #basketballlegends #legends #legendsofthegame #86fleer #fleer #rookie #rookiecard #autographed #signed #autograph #sports #sportsmemorabilia #memorabilia #rare #instagood #instadaily #daily #psadnacertified #authentic #psadna #psacard All posted items are for sale unless otherwise noted! Se bobear foi o jogo mais dominante da equipe na temporada.  É injusto destacar um só atleta, mas tenho que falar do Grant. O rapaz tem substituído muito bem o Rondo e hoje mandou 17 pts e 11 assistências. Seis jogadores dos Bulls fizeram pelo menos 10 pontos, uma prova que o jogo coletivo funcionou muito bem.  Mas vocês não vão acreditar, Miami venceu Cleveland na prorrogação. Sim, isso significa que vamos com o coração na mão para a última rodada na quarta. We just gotta keep moving forward, even if we don't always feel our most positive. We can't allow negative feelings to keep us from moving, otherwise we'll never reach our dreams. Also, shout out to @therealmsmarvel for your post with my video playing. Honestly, it doesn't always occur to me how much what I do really matters to people as I'm going through my day to day stresses, and seeing that first thing in the morning really started the day right. So thank you, for real.

2017, 'Play-Offs' | Las cábalas de los últimos espectros de luz del túnel de 'Play-Offs'. Indiana Pacers (7° con 41-40), Chicago Bulls (8° con 40-41) y Miami Heat (9° con 40-41) están metidos en camisa de 11 balas. Un infortunio, un golpe antes de tiempo, monopolizaría el operativo de clasificación de los demás. - •Chicago Bulls se enfrenta a Brooklyn Nets el miércoles a las 02:00 (hora Española). •Indiana Pacers será visitado por la bandada de Hawks el miércoles a las 02:00 también. •Miami Heat se juega sus fichas restantes en una partida de alto calibre: recibe a los capitalinos Wizards a las, como no, 02:00. - Todas las variantes se hallan en la cuarta foto, que hallaréis deslizando la primera publicación cuya carátula pertenece a James Johnson de Miami Heat. - Ojo, factor clave: •Boston, se mantiene líder del frente Oriental con 52-29 a falta de una batalla contra Milwaukee. •Cleveland se halla estancado en la segunda vacante. Con un 51-30 y una carta más por jugar (contra Toronto Raptors en casa) buscarán la primera plaza. - Eso sí, estas posibilidades les juegan malas pasadas a los dos conjuntos que vayan a pasar como 7° y 8°. Son un calvario. - Básicamente, la búsqueda de la consagración de Miami, Indiana y Chicago como carne de 'Play-Offs' se verá seguida por una oración para que Cleveland se aleje de su enfrentamiento. 📷: @dp7_daniel  #NBA #nba2k17 #League #Basketball #Miami #Heat #Chicago #Bulls #Indiana #Pacers #PG #JB #JJ #Florida #USA #playoffs

🎶On Tone: As flutists, we of course understand the importance of long tones and how practicing them builds the foundation for a gorgeous sound. I, however, rarely utilize long tones anymore, because the slow half step movement no longer engages my brain, nor do I have the time to play long tones in half steps, major 2nds, 3rds, etc. like I feel I should.  I find that exercises like Maquarre or Reichert are PERFECT for practicing consistency of beautiful tone in a more musical context, and perfect for those who don't have hours to spend on tone. I practice half to one full exercise daily, VERY SLOWLY with vibrato, and focus on connecting each interval seamlessly. You can also practice without vibrato if you want to further develop a beautiful sound without it.🎶

I used to not enjoy coming to the city because it felt like everything was cold- the atmosphere, the people, the tall buildings glaring down. Now I live in the city and I feel the coldness creeping in because it's a method of survival. If you're not aware of your surroundings at all times, you will get taken advantage of. Humans are animals, naturally. The truth is I don't want to be cold, I want to remain with my warmth, like that smiling child above, filled with sunshine. I am constantly learning how to balance the many ways of living that us humans have created and it is tough, but what else? With the great privilege of living in the land of opportunity comes a great responsibility to consciously find equilibrium and peace.

#Repost @prep_chicago ・・・ PrEP stands for Pre-Exposure Prophylaxis. PrEP is a pill called Truvada that you take once a day, every day, to help prevent HIV. Pillboxes can help you remember to take PrEP each day. PrEP is for anyone who is HIV negative and at risk for HIV. It does not protect against STIs or pregnancy, so you may need to use condoms or other birth control methods too. Condoms protect against HIV, STIs, and pregnancy. Other birth control methods include the pill, the patch, and IUDs. Not everyone's prevention strategy has to be the same. Know your status and know your risk - then decide what tools you need to keep yourself and your partner(s) safe. . . . #askmeaboutprep #prepchicago #chicago #awareness #healthy #prep #preppill #prepworks #prepfacts #truvada #truvadaforprep #bluepill #hivawareness #hivprevention #HIV #sti #safesex #stiprevention #pregnancyprevention #condoms #birthcontrol #pillbox #pillbottle #pills #prepisforeveryone #dailyprep #bethegeneration #selageneracion

Last night was the night the Cubs raised their banner after Opening Ceremonies. The game was delayed over and hour and Alex Wood made his first spot start of the season. Wood lasted less than 4 innings, allowing 2 runs (1 earned) and with the offense not going anywhere was in line for the loss. Corey Seager got the offense going in the 6th, and in the 7th the Dodgers had the bases loaded with nobody out but were unable to score. In the 8th, Forysthe scored on a error to tie but in the 9th inning after Sergio Romo had exited, Jansen gave up a base hit to score the man from 3rd and the Cubs won on a walk off. Final score 3-2 and the Dodgers drop to 4-4.  The Dodgers are off today, but continue play against the Cubs tomorrow as they get their World Series Rings. The game will against be at 5:05 and it will be Brandon McCarthy against John Lackey. Today I had the pleasure of working with the SAMS organization at a Syrian refugee dental clinic near Amman, Jordan.  We were the second outside medical team to enter this refufee camp. This camp holds over 40,000 refugees. It has a fairly recent hospital and a small two operatory dental clinic. Patients have to walk great distances in the heat to reach these facilities and appointments are months out. For comparison, a medium sized US dental office will have 4 operatories and serve 1500 patients. Though new, these facilities are grossly inadequate for this sized population.  We brought most of our equipment and setup our makeshift clinic in a trailer located in one of the many camp neighborhoods so that residents of that neighborhood would not have to travel far to receive treatment. After a long day or extractions, SDF treatment, and temporary fillings we were invited by some of the kids to play. The simplest games brought smiles to all of our faces. I could see the smiles in the parent's faces as they watched their children laugh and play. It reminded me of the joy my own children give me.  #smilemoredental #dentistry #dentist #teeth #travelandteeth #drdiab #chicago #chicagoland #wheaton #lombard #aurora #love #smilemakeover #smile #teeth #peace #syria #jordan #amman #refugees #syrian #children  #syrianamericanmedicalsociety

I was finally catching up on @jennakutcher's podcast this morning, and @jessclively made a comment that basically said "were taught to look to adults and experts for advice instead of ourselves." Now it's not like that statement is mind blowing, I'm sure we all realize that. I even said to my husband this weekend, talking business, that I knew he couldn't answer my question for me. But why is it that all so often we do look to others instead of ourselves? I mean I'm totally guilty of it!! 🙋🏻 Maybe I'm always wanting things to be too perfect, so I seek some sort of validation when it's not?! Maybe I'm afraid of my own answer. Maybe I'm simply interested in how others view things. I'm still unsure, and probably always will be. Ha. But I do know this, no matter how we come to any conclusions, life still seems to take you on whatever path it feels like. Your goals and plans somehow manifest into something else. Good and Bad! So you're probably wondering where I'm going with this right?! Ha. Basically, don't be afraid of a different path, or have unfavorable outcomes. Just take risks! That's what life is about, and it's exciting! (also, eat almond/fig butter macarons, a lot of them, because they are delicious!) XO

I've always been stubborn, and I hate being told how I'm "supposed" to think or feel.  Growing up, I learned I was "supposed" to hate my freckles. So what did I do? I thought about hating them, then realized how stupid that was. I decided to love them instead.  It's not easy to do this with other aspects of life (I still struggle with loving my chubby body because I'm not "supposed" to). But I try to.  Don't blindly follow what you're told to believe or think or feel. Actively analyze how it affects your life, and go from there ❤️

The old man responds 'Maybe'  The next day his son takes one out for for a ride and breaks his ankle. The neighbour comes by and says, 'that sucks doesn't it.' The old man responds 'Maybe'  The fourth day the country goes to war and all healthy young males are gathered from their homes to be sent off to war, his son with his broken ankle is left behind. His neighbour sees the son left behind and says to the old man 'wow you are so lucky your son has a broke ankle and wasn't chosen for war.' In these two photos we see the console of the 3/21 Kimball the originally resided in the North Center Theatre in Chicago, IL. The organ was originally built by Kimball in 1925 and was installed in the theatre in 1926. After its removal, the organ was stored in deplorable conditions resulting in a great loss of most of the organ itself. The console survived in very rough shape, but it was lovingly restored by a well known enthusiast in Omaha, NE. It now controls a 24 rank Kimball/Wurlitzer hybrid. Although the North Center is gone, the console survived and is living on in a nurturing environment- NR #theatreorgan #theaterorgan #kimballorgan #kimball #organ #chicago #chicagotheatres #chicagotheaters

I've been needing to clean out my phone lately so I was going through older photos I have and it's crazy how much I've changed in the last few months. I was basically starving myself all summer last year. I found myself in an unhealthy relationship, being put under so much pressure about how much I weighed, what And when I was eating, if I was drinking etc. so much to the point of where it was suggested I had lipo done.  This may not seem like a big deal to some but I felt so uncomfortable in my own skin. I was brainwashed that I needed to lose weight and was carrying around constant anxiety. I started skipping meals on purpose and I was exhausted physically and mentally. I called my sister every day telling her I wished I was dead. Life seemed like it would be easier that way. I'm not one to complain but this took a huge toll on my relationships with my family, including my son. Long story short I gave myself a reality check and got out of my unhealthy cycle. I have put on some weight since, which I have struggled with emotionally.  I am so used to beating myself up but after going through these photos and being reminded of where I was emotionally then compared to where I am now is such a difference. Whether I'm lighter or heavier, my heart, mind, and soul are happier now a days and I love the person I am becoming. I have my days where I feel down but every day I grow stronger mentally and physically. I feel more myself now than I ever have. I am working everyday on self compassion and not being so hard on myself.  If you're feeling down or have ever been in a similar situation just breathe and be self aware. Figure out what makes you👉🏼 !JUST YOU! 👈🏼happy. Falling into unhealthy habits is easy to do, then we beat ourselves up for falling into these habits! Don't beat yourself up, forgive yourself and move on! Don't feed into the cycle, break the cycle.  #selflove #selfcompassion #habits #transformationtuesday • • • • • #tuesdaytips #strongnotskinny #toxic #freeyourself #salvation #forgive #loveyourself #health #fitness #dtfw #fitspiration #instagood #instafit #instagirls #chicago #nwi #hairstylist #strong #fitchick #girlswholift #girlswithtattoos #newbeginnings

Judy Chicago was one of the pioneers for the feminist art movement. Throughout her career she has been working to bring issues women are facing to the forefront of art world and get conversations for improvement going. Born in Chicago, she started taking art classes in preschool and continued to pursue them, eventually graduating from @ucla with a Masters in painting and sculpture. In the Spring of 1970 she began teaching a women-only art class at @fresno_state which she referred to as the "Feminist Art Program". A class made up of 15 women renovated an old theatre as their studio where they performed and created activist works of art. In 1972 Chicago paired with Cal Arts to create "Womanhouse" in Hollywood, California. Another platform for creative ways to voice their societal concerns, "Womanhouse" received publicity and helped to push the feminist art movement forward. Perhaps one of her best known projects is "The Dinner Party" (shown here). This massive triangular table consists of 39 place settings, each dedicated to an important woman in history.  The place settings are themed to the contribution of the woman listed, and include textile art as well as ceramics. Along the tile floor below the table there are a series of other names painted in gold. Inspired by a professor who claimed women never made historical contributions, this artwork confronts the viewer with proof of the falsity of his statement. It was conceived with the help of over 400 volunteers and still inspires people to create their own place settings of women they feel should be included in this honorary work. Through depictions of female genitalia in various forms, she takes what is commonly unspoken of (especially at its time of creation) and makes it unavoidable. This artwork promotors a sense of pride for women and showcases how much we have accomplished throughout time🦋On April 26th she has a dry ice installation @sfmoma & TODAY at 12:30 there will be a 15min Linchtime Art Talk on her @hammer_museum 🦋 @judy.chicago #judychicago #chicago #feministart #feminist #revolutionary #feministartmovement #thedinnerparty #uclagraduate #activistart #womanhouse #brooklynmuseum #feminism

Hello everyone! I hope everyone had a happy Easter if you celebrate, and got to spend some time with your loved ones ☺️ Here's some of the delicious food I got to eat yesterday plus a few other things. 🙆🏽 I know the holidays can be stressful with all the different kinds of food when you have fitness related goals. But something that's helped me a lot is to not think about the food so much. Yes, the food is present and it's there but is that REALLY what the holidays about? No. enjoy yourself and your time you have with the people closest to you because those are memories you won't get back. - -Another thing people have a hard time with (I know because I used to feel the same way) is thinking they HAVE TO say no all the time or you HAVE TO say yes all the time. You DO NOT have to say yes to the chocolate cake every time it's offered to you, but you also DO NOT have to say no every time either 😊 chicken and fruit n veggies and your whole grains are good for your muscles and your body , but I know for me personally chocolate is good for my soul and just as important 😉😋🍫
Just a touch of your love 💚

Tal día como hoy, pero en 1956, debuta Don #LuisAparicio, en las #GrandesLigas. Fue el primer año de una extensa carrera llena de éxitos, hazañas y grandes logros en el big show.  En esa primera temporada, Aparicio, dio muestra del gran talento que se venía con la organización de los #ChicagoWhiteSox, al coronarse líder en bases robadas con 21, (una cadena de liderazgo que tuvo en 9 campañas seguidas en ese departamento), así mismo, fue galardonado con el premio de #NovatoDelAño en la #LigaAmericana, con el 92% de los votos, convirtiéndose en el primer latino en las mayores con esa distinción.  No cabe duda, que el zuliano, desde que pisó por vez primera un terreno de grandes ligas, fue lleno de grandes éxitos donde culminó en el Salón de la Fama en 1984, siendo el primer y único criollo que reposa su placa en el templo de los inmortales, en la #MLB. Defining "true friends" is very hard these days with the "All about me" attitude and separating true friends from the opportunist and users who just need you for what you have or can do for them.  I have to say in these 2 on this photo with me and other's (you know who you are), that I have an abundance of true friends and I thank God for them everyday! Every time I'm out in Chicago I always think about one of my favorite words: Sonder. It's the "realization that arch random passerby is living a life as vivid and complex as your own - populated with their own ambitions, friends, routines, worries and inherited craziness - an epic story that continues invisibly around you like an anthill sprawling deep underground, with elaborate passageways to thousands of other lives that you’ll never know existed, in which you might appear only once, as an extra sipping coffee in the background, as a blur of traffic passing on the highway, as a lighted window at dusk." I'll never know where these people are off to but I love imagining where it might be. - - - #chicago #chitecture #architecture #passerby #sonder #inspiration #quote #psychology #philosophy #blackandwhite #chicagogram #photography #chitown #chishots #downtown #urban #instagram #instadaily #instagood #picoftheday #photooftheday #chigers #igers

📖Éste hermoso libro lleva consigo un gran mensaje de amor ❤️ Quienes tengan la oportunidad de leerlo aprovéchenlo, se lee súper rápido y el aprendizaje es grande 🙌🏻 Aquí les dejo una porción 🍰 del libro 😄 El amor está compuesto de nueve ingredientes: Paciencia: El amor es paciente. Benigno: Es benigno. Generosidad: El amor no se consume en celos. Humildad: No se vanagloria, no se enorgullece. Delicadeza: No se conduce inconvenientemente. Entrega: No busca sus intereses. Tolerancia: No se exaspera. Inocencia: No se resiente del mal. Sinceridad: No se alegra con la injusticia, sino que se regocija con la verdad. Todos esos dones están relacionados con nosotros, con nuestra vida diaria, con el hoy y con el mañana, con la eternidad. Siempre escuchamos hablar mucho del amor a Dios. Pero Cristo nos habla del amor al hombre. Buscamos La Paz en los Cielos. Cristo busca La Paz en la Tierra. ✨🙏🏻✨ P.D.: Cafecito con aceite de coco ☕️🌴☺️ #LograzzoPlanner

Art spans a broad spectrum - GIVE THANKS Challenge #leadersofthenewschool  The new Havas Worldwide Intern draft has started! The give thanks challenge is all about an employee appreciation day and how exactly the company can celebrate. Walking around the city last night, snapping photos, reminded me how vast the Chicago Theater District really is (in the loop as well as other neighborhoods). We are lucky enough to get some of the best plays and musicals being performed right at our finger tips. Personally, when ever I feel stuck, either in photography or in writing, I take time to experience art in a new way. Sometimes by simply spending time scrolling the internet or getting out of the house and to a museum. Seeing how other people create can be both inspiring and a refreshing break from what ever I'm working on. I believe getting the employee's out of the office for a day to see what our city has to offer from these historic theaters (whether that be Rick Ross or Aladdin: The Musical, depending on your taste) would not only show our appreciation for them but also inspire them to look at task from a different light and be able to come up with creative new ideas. It can act as a reset button for everyone's mind! - @havasnewschool @havaschi 📷: Georgia Modi

Logan Boulevard) in Chicago. The double-header kicks off with Chicago Outfit Roller Derby's Shade Brigade vs. Royal City Roller Girls' Rum Rollers(B) from Ontario, Canada at 7:00 pm, and the excitement keeps rolling with The Outfit’s Syndicate vs. Royal City's Brute Leggers (A).⠀ ⠀ Tickets can be purchased online for $15 at http://bit.ly/2nEKnj6, or at the door for $20. Discounts are available for groups of 10 or more.⠀ ⠀ Partial proceeds will support Connections for Abused Women and their Children, a domestic violence shelter in Chicago which also offers counseling, advocacy, and a 24-hour hotline for people affected by domestic violence. http://www.cawc.org/⠀ ⠀ Additional treats and entertainment will be available for all to enjoy. Beer provided courtesy of Lagunitas Brewing Co will be available for purchase. El impulsor de Hollywood, en contra de su voluntad, fue Thomas Alva Edison. Ya veremos porque.  Los Hermanos Lumière registraron el cinematógrafo el 13 de febrero de 1894.  Edison, como buen visionario, vio este invento como un gran negocio y le compró la patente a estos chicos franceses. Comercializó en la costa Este de EE.UU la nueva tecnología, vendiendo los derechos a todos aquellos que querían explotarlo. Si alguien quería utilizar el cinematoógrafo sin permiso de Mr Thomas, este enviaba a sus "matones" o "pistoleros"  a eliminar las intenciones del usurpador.  Estás nuevas productoras, viendo lo peligroso y hostil que se tornaba trabajar en esta parte del mapa (Chicago o New York) optaron por huir al punto más lejos que podían, la costa oeste, cerca de los Ángeles, en un pequeño pueblo llamado Hollywood, donde Edison no poseía derechos de explotación  No todo lo que brilla es oro. Muchos inventos exitosos tienen historias tristes. Fue Hollywood, el mismo que hoy en día defiende tanto los derechos de autor de sus películas, el primero que se levantó contra el monopolio del cine que tenía el inventor de la bombilla. Que ironías tiene la historia. #edison #tudatohistorico #history #historia #hollywood #newyork #chicago #cine #movies #patente #lumiere #francia #paris #mafias #este #oeste #losangeles #california #mundo #inventos

This business has been amazing for me and I’ve had the chance to meet and work with supportive women from all over the country. "This is the thing: When you hit 28 or 30, everything begins to divide. You can see very clearly two kinds of people. On one side, people who have used their 20s to learn and grow, to find themselves and their dreams, people who know what works and what doesn’t, who have pushed through to become real live adults. Then there’s the other kind, who are hanging onto college, or high school even, with all their might. They’ve stayed in jobs they hate, because they’re too scared to get another one. They’ve stayed with men or women who are good but not great, because they don’t want to be lonely. They mean to develop intimate friendships, they mean to stop drinking like life is one big frat party. But they don’t do those things, so they live in an extended adolescence, no closer to adulthood than when they graduated.  Don’t be like that. Don’t get stuck. Move, travel, take a class, take a risk. There is a season for wildness and a season for settledness, and this is neither. This season is about becoming." - @pourlesrebelles

Fountain of Time, or simply Time, is a sculpture by Lorado Taft, measuring 126 feet 10 inches (38.66 m) in length, situated at the western edge of the Midway Plaisance within Washington Park in Chicago, Illinois, in the United States. This location is in the Washington Park community area on Chicago's South Side. Inspired by Henry Austin Dobson's poem "Paradox of Time", and with its 100 figures passing before Father Time, the work was created as a monument to the first 100 years of peace between the United States and Great Britain, resulting from the Treaty of Ghent in 1814. Although the fountain's water began running in 1920, the sculpture was not dedicated to the city until 1922. The sculpture is a contributing structure to the Washington Park United States Registered Historic District, which is a National Register of Historic Places listing. #fountainoftime #washingtonpark #chicago #southside #photography #nikon #nikond3400 #photo #statue #fountain #art #night
